"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-01-28-hibbert-targets-olympic-world-u20-double\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"KINGSTON, Jamaica- Jamaica's two-time men's triple jump champion Jaydon Hibbert is targeting a unique Olympic Games/World Under -20 double for this season, he said in a virtual press conference on Sunday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 26, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.999993593024162, \"rank\": 6.231244601556826e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 72, \"end\": 79, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\", \"score\": 0.9775502384392023, \"rank\": 0.022965317104906225, \"text\": \"Hibbert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hibbert, who signed a professional contract last week, but would still attend classes at the University of Arkansas, said he was bypassing the indoor (short track) season and would be focussed on the outdoor season.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\", \"score\": 0.9775502384392023, \"rank\": 0.022965317104906225, \"text\": \"Hibbert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toots_Hibbert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has\\u00a0prioritised four events:\\u00a0the Olympic Games, the JAAA National Championships, the Diamond League and the World Under- 20.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 478, \"end\": 482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Athletics_Administrative_Association\", \"s